MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5a3a40b1ee4441518f69c26c62cb3cde, type: 3}
  m_Name: Book_Level_04_Raven_Intro
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueData
  dialogueId: book_level_04_raven_intro
  lines:
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 12d337519c78aa44cb9dca67ae4afc03, type: 2}
    speakerName: Raven
    text: Daughter of the steppe, I saw the smoke of your fires long before it turned
      black. At first, people warmed their hands by the flame. Then they began to
      warm their pride with it.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6992f1ad55b7805439d6200abb695e15, type: 2}
    speakerName: Aisulu
    text: I am not walking this path to justify people. I am walking it to understand
      whether light can be returned to those who have forgotten its price.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 12d337519c78aa44cb9dca67ae4afc03, type: 2}
    speakerName: Raven
    text: The price of fire is not in brushwood, nor in the spark. Its price is in
      the memory that people lose faster than ash cools in the wind.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6992f1ad55b7805439d6200abb695e15, type: 2}
    speakerName: Aisulu
    text: Then if I find the fire, I must bring home not only the flame, but also
      the memory of why it was given.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
  - speakerProfile: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 12d337519c78aa44cb9dca67ae4afc03, type: 2}
    speakerName: Raven
    text: Fine words, daughter of the steppe. But words rarely win where shadow has
      already made its home. Fly on, if you can... but this time, victory will not
      choose you.
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
